## Useful Commands

View running containers:

docker ps

View app logs:

docker logs {{ slug }}

View database logs:

docker logs {{ db_container }}

Open MariaDB shell as root:

docker exec -it {{ db_container }} mariadb -uroot -p

Open MariaDB shell as app user:

docker exec -it {{ db_container }} mariadb -u{{ db_user }} -p {{ db_name }}

Restart project:

cd {{ project_path }}
docker compose restart

Stop project:

cd {{ project_path }}
docker compose down

Start project:

cd {{ project_path }}
docker compose up -d

Backup database:

docker exec {{ db_container }} mariadb-dump -uroot -p {{ db_name }} > {{ db_name }}_backup.sql

## Important Notes

The MariaDB port is not published to the local network by default.

The database is only reachable by containers inside the Docker network.

The database data is stored in the Docker volume:

{{ db_volume }}

Do not delete the volume unless you intend to delete the database data.
